The paper deals with the demand-flow of agents with gross-substitute valuations, which is a topic in computational game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic economics (cs.EC). The paper also uses mathematical tools such as partial orders and lattice theory, which are common in discrete mathematics (cs.DS).
